content.description: Nice granite line on a clean boulder with not a horrible landing. The line starts low and left with a good jug-shelf and excellent right foot. From there work up the nobs, matches, and crimps to a big reach for a high, right crimp. The hold is good but definitely the crux of the problem! From there cross-over and it’s smooth sailing to the top.Probably been climbed before, if anyone has info do tell but for now...FA: Cole Ortagus & Keenan Hammack
content.protection: 1-3 pads, ankle roller rocks below first few moves
content.location: From the animal hospital parking lot follow a series of washes and hobo trails uphill about 300 yards. The boulder is south facing near the top of the first major pile.

content.description: Good granite boulders with a few decent landings. Low-highballs and traverses galore. There is definitely great potential in this pile.
